===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|cycen|ċȳcen|lang=ang}}, diminuitive of {{term|cocc|lang=ang}} "cock, rooster" (i.e. ''cocc'', ''cucc'' + ''-en'', ''-in''). More at [[cock]], [[-en]]

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/'tʃɪk.ɪn/}}, {{SAMPA|/"tSIkIn/}}
* {{audio|en-us-chicken.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪkɪn}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{countable}} A domestic [[fowl]], ''Gallus gallus'', especially when young
# {{uncountable}} The meat from this bird eaten as food.
# {{context|countable|slang}} A [[coward]].
# {{countable|gay slang}} A young, attractive, slim man, usually having little body hair.
# {{context|countable|slang}} A young person of either sex.
# A [[confrontational]] [[game]] in which the participants move toward each other at high speed (usually in [[automobile]]s); the player who turns first to avoid colliding into the other is the [[loser]].

